{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Insert simmering basket. Place water in mixing bowl.","Weigh rice into simmering basket and steam <b>16 min\/Varoma\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, place vinegar, sugar and ½ tsp salt in a small bowl. Stir until grains are dissolved, then set aside.","Leave simmering basket in position for a couple of minutes to drain, remove with aid of spatula and transfer steamed rice to a large non-metal shallow dish, then sprinkle vinegar mixture all over. Using a soft spatula, toss gently to distribute vinegar mixture then leave to cool. Discard steaming water.","Place surimi sticks, cream cheese, sriracha sauce and ¼ tsp salt in mixing bowl then chop <b>2 sec\/speed 4<b>.","Place a sheet of nori, shiny side down on a bamboo sushi mat then gently spread ¼ prepared sushi rice over nori sheet with a wet, soft spatula (see tip), leaving ⅓ clear at the far end. Lay ¼ of seafood mixture, cucumber matchsticks and avocado slices on rice across the end closest to you then, using bamboo sushi mat, begin rolling tightly to form a roll. Before reacing the end brush edge of nori with vinegar-water mixture (see tip) to help seal the roll then continue rolling. Set finished roll aside then continue assembling remaining rolls.","To serve, slice each roll into 1.5 cm pieces using a wet, sharp knife then serve with soy sauce, for dipping."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1000 g water, plus extra for brushing","250 g sushi rice, rinsed well","2 Tbsp rice vinegar, plus 2 Tbsp for brushing","1 tsp caster sugar","¾ tsp fine sea salt","120 g surimi sticks","80 g cream cheese","1 Tbsp sriracha sauce (chilli sauce)","200 g cucumber, deseeded, cut in matchsticks","½ avocado, thinly sliced","4 sheets nori seaweed","soy sauce, for dipping"]}],"id":"r207881","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/--dQXnl5i0Hw\/XZapoE_wYCI\/AAAAAAAAhS8\/71b4CB7ma3opvtM01INtV_jU2IJIVU84QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_5-kK1T_ANFGwG0sW.png","title":"Seafood and Cream Cheese Rolls","publishedAt":"2017-08-21T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.2 g","fat":"0.9 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"5.5 g","calories":"156 kJ \/ 37 kcal"},"usefulItems":"shallow bowl or dish, pastry brush, sharp knife, silicone spatula, bamboo sushi mat","hintsAndTricks":["Many people think sushi means raw fish, but it is actually a reference to vinegared rice combined with various ingredients.","Place <b>200 g<b> water and <b>2 Tbsp<b> rice vinegar in a bowl to use for brushing and keeping hands and utensils wet so they don't stick to the rice.","Traditionally sushi rice should be body temperature rather than chilled, therefore for optimum quality, sushi is best served immediately or within a few hours of making. Wrap rolls in cling film and leave in a cool dry place then slice just before serving.","Sushi can be wrapped in cling film and refrigerated. Consume within <b>24 hours<b> but be mindful that the quality decreases quickly due to the rice losing moisture.","Sriracha is a hot, chilli sauce made from a paste of chili peppers, vinegar, garlic, sugar and salt. It is typically used as a dipping sauce or to accompany seafood."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 20m","36 pieces"]}